sub_title: ICF Master Certified Coach MCC, Mentor, EMCC Supervisor, Facilitator, Trainer
summary:
I help ambitious individuals to define and live their personal paths of success.  Specifically, I catalyse the growth of emerging leaders, the transformation of senior executives and board members of leading corporations through in-person and virtual/remote individual and group sessions.   

In addition, as an ICF MCC (Master Certified Coach, approx. 1200 business leaders, 8000 coaching hours) and Certified Mentor Coach, I help the candidates to achieve the desired ICF credentials.  As an EMCC accredited supervisor, I nurture the wellbeing and practice of aspirational coaches.  At the same time, I teach in ICF accredited executive coaching programmes. 

My clients include numerous notable technology companies (for example cloud-based applications for CRM, learning, digital transformation etc.), London Business School (LBS), LVMH Group (Louis Vuitton Moët Hennessy) and World Food Programme.  With LBS, I am an active contributor to the Executive Education and the EMBA programmes. I coach and facilitate in various (custom and open) leading change and transformation themed programmes for companies such as Air Liquide, Kearney, BMW, EY, ING, KPMG, MARS,  Nestlé and Roche etc.. 

Prior to becoming independent, I have had an extensive 10-year career in HRD and business management.  I have been a regular recipient of awards in People Developer, Retail Management and Performance Management.  My industry experience lies in leadership and engagement, creating business value & talent development. 

Born in Singapore, I am fluent in English, Mandarin and Cantonese.  I’m able to converse in Dutch and French at a social level. Currently, I divide my time in Amsterdam, London, Nice and Singapore for work and residence.    

My clients tend to focus their development on these themes:
* Working on your best self
* Life and work crafting
* Shaping your environment for sustainable growth                
* Transformational leadership which focuses on relationships building
* Virtual & International Team Leadership
* Strategic Leadership
